Hy folks,

I would like to run my pypiserver behind a nginx proxy (reverse proxy). 
Accessing pypiserver _directly_ (using `pip3 install --extra-index-url http://pypiserver.example.com:12345 moduletest` on a client) works fine.

Proxied browsing through the repository using a browser (i.e. `http://myproxy.example.com/simple/moduletest`) works fine. `Nginx conf`:

```
upstream pypi {
  server pypiserver.example.com:12345 fail_timeout=0;
}

server {
  server_name myproxy.example.com;

  location / {
    proxy_set_header  Host $host;
    proxy_set_header  X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
    # no effect: proxy_set_header  X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
    # no effect: proxy_set_header  X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    proxy_pass http://pypi;
  }
}
```

Obviously pip is not able to find any package when accessing pypiserver via _proxy_, like `pip3 install --extra-index-url http://myproxy.example.com moduletest` on a client, returning:

```
Could not find a version that satisfies the requirement moduletest (from versions: )
No matching distribution found for moduletest
```

I assume, that's a newbie issue? I'd appreciate your support.

Thank you
ITler
